nts1.n: THE EARLY BIRD SHOW W/ MARIA SOMERVILLE
nts1.d: Drifting into a new day with Maria Somerville, live from Ireland's wild west coast.

nts1.n: The NTS Breakfast Show w/ LAURA GROVES

nts1.d: Listen in for positivity and light as Anu broadcasts through the afternoon.

London-based DJ and producer Nabihah Iqbal (formerly known as Throwing Shade) brings you an ethnomusicological perspective on weird and wonderful music from around the world. Expect regular themed special episode; a good dose of history, and above all, good music to broaden your horizons. Every other Tuesday, midday-1pm. You can listen back to previous Throwing Shade episodes here
Settle in for weekly shows from Margeaux aka @marg.mp3, soothing with an hour of selections, offering an eclectic range of sounds old and new.
Record collector, artist, and mystic, Millie McKee shares organic spirtualized oddities and stories, dancing between rare variations of jazz, psych, dub and rock and more.

nts1.n: CHANNELING W/ IVAN SMAGGHE & NATHAN GREGORY WILKINS
nts1.d: Old friends and hapless mavericks Ivan Smagghe and Nathan Gregory Wilkins present a fortnightly window into their ramshackle musical world. A show with absolutely no rules (as they'd only break them). We love the unmixable, old & new. We are oddballs and we love you.

Veronica Vasicka presents a monthly 2-hour show featuring the lost synth-wave treasures she has archived from the late 70s and early 80s, along with other iconic underground electronic music drawn from over four decades. Expect to hear exclusive tracks from releases on her seminal Minimal Wave and Cititrax labels plus cassette-only and private press rarities.
Connections in electronic music: the history of house and techno as presented to you by the wonderful Olly Chubb.

nts2.n: The Head Zone w/ Ripley Johnson (R)
nts2.d: Step into The Head Zone - one hour of musical selections from the mind of Moon Duo's Ripley Johnson.

nts2.n: PLAY IT AS IT LATHES W/ ZACH COWIE (R)
nts2.d: Zach Cowie - former record label guy & DJ turned music supervisor. Every month Zach lays down a vinyl-only one hour mix of ambient, experimental, folk, psych and jazz records with Play It As It Lathes.

nts2.n: Nordic Archive w/ Sara Parkman & Mats Erlandsson
nts2.d:
Folk innovator Sara Parkman and drone composer and producer Mats Erlandsson share their mutual love of the Nordic folk music tradition with an hour of archival and contemporary recordings.
Traversing Northern Europe via herding calls, modal hymns, solo fiddle, and electronics.
A bi-montly collage of acoustic and electronic sound in our current orbit. Probs seasonal. Sometimes fickle.
Regular transmissions from two of Glasgow's most idiosyncratic & knowledgable DJs.

nts2.n: Chasing echoes w/ TOHÉ COMMARET + ARIANE KIKS
nts2.d:
Independent film director and contemporary artist Tohé Commaret and photographer and DJ Ariane Kiks drift into the inner worlds of real and imagined figures on Chasing Echoes – each episode blends archival voices, intimate writings, and imagined soundscapes, chasing echoes of memory and presence.
From the host: "She disappeared into the blur."
Skinny Girl Diet are London's foremost riot grrrl duo. Delilah Holliday and Ursula Holliday. Post-punk, glam, garage and all things nice… or something like that.

NahhG hosts Tuesday Trips, exploring the different sounds of underground beats and hip-hop alongside special guest mixes from current beatmakers and curators. - Live once a month
From the host: "Starting off the first show of the year with a mix from my older brother, DJ Blessthagawd. He returns with his second mix for the show playing nothing but modern hip-hop classics. Enjoy this one of a kind mix!"

"It's the yearly 90s Rnb & Slow Jams Valentine's Day Mix.
This one is for all the lovers, yearners, hopeful romantics, and the grown & sexy. Cheers! xoxoxo -Abby"
Cuban record collector, ethnomusicologist researcher, picks up a hour of global vinyl via Havana every months.

Curator and DJ Edna Martinez explores the champeta, an underground musical genre and dance that originated in the Caribbean coast of Colombia in the early 1980s. The rhythms and influences are said to have arrived with the sailors from West Africa in the 1960s and 70s. We will get to know in each episode its specificities and the relevance of this scene.
From the host: "This episode is dedicated to the memory of Dogar Disc (Ismael Simancas), one of the pioneering voices of champeta from Cartagena. With over three decades of work, his music helped shape sound of the city and the genre itself. This show is a small tribute to his legacy and history he leaves behind."
Memphis selector and radio host Nya presents an hour of rare soul, boogie, gospel, and funk records once a month.
Every month Jonah Rabb brings you Weekend Read, an hour of funk, house, contemporary R&B, and more.

nts2.n: NTS Guide to: South And South East Asian Garage
nts2.j: South And South East Asian Garage

subtle.d: Hailing from northern Italy, STANDARD is a collective of artists, DJs and producers that aims at the promotion of bass music: Garage, UK Funky, Breaks, Leftfield Bass, Leftfield Techno, Dubstep, everything in between and beyond. They focus on the Italian Bass scene, showcasing new up-and-coming artists as well as established talents from all over the peninsula.

Oddkut is a producer & DJ hailing from Balakovo City, Russia. He's part of the Russian collective "United Gang" who are a Moscow-based community of local musicians, DJ's and promoters teamed up by their genuine love & interest in UK underground music, "TAЭT VREMYA" art group and the creator of the Moscow parties "Judder".

subtle.n: A Step Forward w/ Gregoire Yasmine

subtle.d: Established in 2013, eatmybeat is a hybrid record label & club brand that was brought together by a group of friends with a passion for electronic music and building community. With diverse tastes, they support and champion the underground bass music scene through events and releases on the label. Refusing to be pigeonholed into a specific sound, they showcase everything from hip-hop, bass & breaks, through to techno, jungle, dubstep and grime. As long as it's tasty and full fat, you best believe eatmybeat are snacking on it.

dublab.d: “Dying Songs focuses on melancholic electronic music but isn’t limited to that. Sometimes it gets dark, sometimes I try to mix techno awkwardly, sometimes i get nostalgic… I like stuff that’s dreamy, ghostly, pretty and sad. I’ll try out new productions of my own, as well. I’m keeping it pretty open and we’ll see how it evolves.” – Jimmy

dublab.n: Daddy Differently and Dirty Dave - Things of Life
dublab.d: It’s the simple things isn’t it? The little things of life. Good food, sunshine, no traffic, dark coffee, 72˚ breeze, telephone off the hook and music every Friday morning a la Daddy Differently & Dirty Dave.
